## 2. Layer Definitions

### 2.1 Domain Layer (`src/domain/`)

The **innermost layer**. Zero dependencies on Node.js, Prisma, Octokit, or Express. Contains only:

| Sub-layer | Contents | Rule |
|-----------|----------|------|
| `entities/` | `Repo.ts`, `Metrics.ts`, `TrendingRepo.ts` | Pure TypeScript interfaces/classes, no imports from outside domain |
| `usecases/` | `AnalyzeRepo.ts`, `GetTrending.ts` | Depend on Port interfaces only — never on concrete adapters |

**Entity definitions:**

```typescript
// domain/entities/Repo.ts
export interface Repo {
  owner: string;
  name: string;
  fullName: string;
  description: string | null;
  stars: number;
  forks: number;
  openIssues: number;
  defaultBranch: string;
  pushedAt: Date;
  createdAt: Date;
}

// domain/entities/Metrics.ts
export interface Metrics {
  repoOwner: string;
  repoName: string;
  stars: number;
  starGrowth24h: string;        // e.g. "+142 (0.8%)"
  languages: Record<string, number>;
  openIssues: number;
  contributors: number;
  lastCommit: Date;
  analyzedAt: Date;
}

// domain/entities/TrendingRepo.ts
export interface TrendingRepo {
  owner: string;
  name: string;
  stars: number;
  starGrowth24h: string;
  primaryLanguage: string | null;
  description: string | null;
}
```

**Use Case: AnalyzeRepo** — core orchestration:

```
analyzeRepo(owner, repo, deep)
  │
  ├── 1. repoApiPort.getRepo(owner, repo)          → fetch live data from GitHub
  ├── 2. repoApiPort.getLanguages(owner, repo)     → language breakdown
  ├── 3. [if deep] repoApiPort.getIssues(...)      → issue count verification
  ├── 4. metricsRepoPort.getMetrics(owner, repo)   → load previous snapshot
  ├── 5. compute starGrowth24h from delta
  ├── 6. metricsRepoPort.saveMetrics(computed)     → persist / update cache
  └── 7. return Metrics
```

---

### 2.2 Ports Layer (`src/ports/`)

**Contracts (interfaces only)** — no implementation code. These are the "holes" in the hexagon.

```typescript
// ports/RepoApiPort.ts
export interface RepoApiPort {
  getRepo(owner: string, repo: string): Promise<Repo>;
  getLanguages(owner: string, repo: string): Promise<Record<string, number>>;
  getIssues(owner: string, repo: string): Promise<number>;
}

// ports/MetricsRepoPort.ts
export interface MetricsRepoPort {
  saveMetrics(data: Metrics): Promise<void>;
  getMetrics(owner: string, repo: string): Promise<Metrics | null>;
  getTrending(language?: string): Promise<TrendingRepo[]>;
}
```

---

### 2.3 Adapters Layer (`src/adapters/`)

**Concrete implementations** of ports. Can be swapped without touching domain code.

#### GithubAdapter (`adapters/github/GithubAdapter.ts`)

```
GithubAdapter
  implements RepoApiPort
  uses: @octokit/rest
  env: GITHUB_TOKEN (via constructor injection)

  getRepo()        → GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}
  getLanguages()   → GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/languages
  getIssues()      → GET /repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues?state=open&per_page=1
                     (reads X-Total-Count or pagination hint)
```

Rate limiting: Octokit auto-handles 403/429 with retry. Authenticated = 5000 req/hr.

#### PrismaAdapter (`adapters/database/PrismaAdapter.ts`)

```
PrismaAdapter
  implements MetricsRepoPort
  uses: @prisma/client
  env: DATABASE_URL

  saveMetrics()    → upsert on (repoOwner, repoName)
  getMetrics()     → findUnique by composite key
  getTrending()    → findMany WHERE analyzedAt > now-24h
                     ORDER BY starGrowth DESC
                     optional WHERE primaryLanguage = lang
```

---

### 2.4 Server Layer (`src/server/`)

**Driving adapters** — they receive input and call use cases.

#### Express (`server/express.ts`)

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  Express App (port 3005)                             │
│                                                      │
│  GET  /health                                        │
│       → { status: "ok", ts: ISO8601 }               │
│                                                      │
│  POST /repos/:owner/:repo/analyze                    │
│       body: { deep?: boolean }                       │
│       → AnalyzeRepo.execute(owner, repo, deep)       │
│       ← Metrics (JSON)                              │
│                                                      │
│  GET  /repos/:owner/:repo                            │
│       → MetricsRepoPort.getMetrics(owner, repo)     │
│       ← Metrics | 404                               │
│                                                      │
│  GET  /trending/:language?                           │
│       → GetTrending.execute(language?)              │
│       ← TrendingRepo[]                              │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

Error handling: Global error middleware maps domain errors → HTTP status codes.

#### MCP Server (`server/mcp.ts`)

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  MCP Server (stdio transport)                        │
│  SDK: @modelcontextprotocol/typescript-sdk           │
│                                                      │
│  Tool: analyze_repo                                  │
│    input: { owner: string, repo: string,            │
│             deep?: boolean }                         │
│    calls: AnalyzeRepo.execute(...)                  │
│    returns: Metrics as JSON text                    │
│                                                      │
│  Tool: get_trending                                  │
│    input: { language?: string }                     │
│    calls: GetTrending.execute(...)                  │
│    returns: TrendingRepo[] as JSON text             │
└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

