## 3. Data Flow Diagrams

### 3.1 POST /repos/:owner/:repo/analyze

```
HTTP Client
    │
    ▼
Express Router
    │  (owner, repo, deep)
    ▼
AnalyzeRepo.execute()
    │
    ├──▶ GithubAdapter.getRepo()
    │         │
    │         ▼ Octokit → GitHub REST API
    │         ◀ Repo data
    │
    ├──▶ GithubAdapter.getLanguages()
    │         │
    │         ▼ Octokit → GitHub REST API
    │         ◀ { TypeScript: 45000, ... }
    │
    ├──▶ PrismaAdapter.getMetrics()      ← load previous snapshot
    │         │
    │         ▼ Prisma → PostgreSQL
    │         ◀ Metrics | null
    │
    │   [compute growth delta]
    │
    ├──▶ PrismaAdapter.saveMetrics()     ← upsert cache
    │         │
    │         ▼ Prisma → PostgreSQL
    │
    ◀ Metrics (JSON)
    │
    ▼
HTTP 200 { stars, starGrowth24h, languages, ... }
```

### 3.2 Dependency Injection (Wiring at startup)

```typescript
// src/index.ts
const githubAdapter    = new GithubAdapter(process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN);
const prismaAdapter    = new PrismaAdapter(prismaClient);

const analyzeRepo      = new AnalyzeRepo(githubAdapter, prismaAdapter);
const getTrending      = new GetTrending(prismaAdapter);

const expressApp       = createExpressApp(analyzeRepo, getTrending, prismaAdapter);
const mcpServer        = createMcpServer(analyzeRepo, getTrending);
```

**The domain never imports adapters. Adapters never import each other.**

