## 8. Testing Strategy

Each layer is independently testable:

| Layer | Test Type | Approach |
|-------|-----------|----------|
| Domain entities | Unit | Pure TypeScript, no mocks needed |
| Use cases | Unit | Inject mock ports (jest.fn() / vi.fn()) |
| Adapters | Integration | Use real GitHub sandbox / local Postgres |
| HTTP endpoints | Integration | Supertest against real Express instance |
| MCP tools | Integration | MCP SDK in-process test client |

**Example use case test:**
```typescript
const mockRepoApi: RepoApiPort = {
  getRepo: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue(fakeRepo),
  getLanguages: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue({ TypeScript: 50000 }),
  getIssues: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue(12),
};
const mockMetricsRepo: MetricsRepoPort = {
  saveMetrics: jest.fn(),
  getMetrics: jest.fn().mockResolvedValue(null),
  getTrending: jest.fn(),
};

const useCase = new AnalyzeRepo(mockRepoApi, mockMetricsRepo);
const result = await useCase.execute("facebook", "react", false);

expect(result.stars).toBe(fakeRepo.stars);
expect(mockMetricsRepo.saveMetrics).toHaveBeenCalledOnce();
```

